  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <p xml:id="NA395-kiḷavi">itu nalantolaintatu.</p>
            <p xml:lang="en">This is how the innocence was lost.</p>
            </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA395">
<l>            yārai yeluva yāmē nīyemak</l>
<l>            kiyāraiyu mallai notuma lāḷaṉai</l>
<l>            yaṉaittāṟ koṇkavem miṭaiyē niṉaippiṟ</l>
<l>            kaṭumpakaṭ ṭiyāṉai neṭuntērk kuṭṭuvaṉ</l>
<l>            vēntaṭu kaḷattiṉ muracatirn taṉṉa</l>
<l>            vōṅkaṟ puṇari pāyntāṭu makaḷi</l>
<l>            raṇintiṭu palpū marīi yārnta</l>
<l>            vāpulam pukutaru pēricai mālaik</l>
<l>            kaṭalkeḻu māntai yaṉṉavem</l>
<l>            vēṭṭaṉai yallaiyā ṉalantantu ceṉmē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>            Who [are] you, friend(?)?</l>
<l rend="indent4">            We, for us you</l>
<l>        are nobody at all, you [are] a stranger.</l>
<l>        Thus it [is] indeed, man from the sea, between us.</l>
<l rend="indent4">            If you think so,</l>
<l rend="indent">            like sea-bound Māntai at famous/noisy(?) evening,</l>
<l rend="indent2">            when the cows enter from the field(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">pulam</term>: here we have a semantic problem. The context (and the topos too) require the cows to come back home in the evening. Do we have to assume that <term xml:lang="ta">pulam</term>, perhaps in connection with puku, can be used as a synonym of <term xml:lang="ta">maṉṟam</term>? Or do we simply take it as ablative?</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent3">            that had fed joining the many flowers, used for decoration</l>
<l rend="indent3">            [and] cast away by women frolicking [and] playing in the rising ocean,</l>
<l rend="indent4">            resounding like a drum on the field where kings are killed</l>
<l rend="indent4">            by Kuṭṭuvaṉ with long chariot [and] fierce bull elephants,</l>
<l>        you didn’t want us indeed.</l>
<l rend="indent4">             Give [back our] innocence [and] go!<note place="foot">For the <term xml:lang="ta">nalam</term> given back to HER cf. KT 236, 238.</note></l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
